55:05.000 --> 55:11.000
Lecture 2. Structure, Composition and Classification of IT and IT systems

55:11.000 --> 55:16.000
First, let's consider the concept of IT and IT systems.

55:16.000 --> 55:25.000
The concept of IT is usually associated with operations on data and information,

55:25.000 --> 55:31.000
such as storage, processing, transfer or exchange of data or information.

55:31.000 --> 55:37.000
The concept of IT is usually associated with the final set of hardware and software complexes

55:38.000 --> 55:45.000
and various resources that serve certain informational and management purposes.

55:45.000 --> 55:51.000
The slide shows the IT as a process of data and information transfer.

55:51.000 --> 55:54.000
So, we have the structure of IT,

55:54.000 --> 55:59.000
which at a certain level is split into information processes.

55:59.000 --> 56:02.000
At another level, the information process is distributed

56:03.000 --> 56:05.000
according to information procedures,

56:05.000 --> 56:10.000
which in turn are divided according to information operations.

56:10.000 --> 56:16.000
Here, in fact, the model of the detailing of the process of data transfer is depicted.

56:16.000 --> 56:18.000
This is the most general and formal model

56:18.000 --> 56:21.000
that allows to describe the processes of obtaining, displaying,

56:21.000 --> 56:25.000
accumulating, processing, transfer of data and information,

56:25.000 --> 56:28.000
as well as the procedures and operations of collection, preparation,

56:28.000 --> 56:32.000
formatting, archiving, search, conversion, logical conclusion,

56:32.000 --> 56:36.000
commutation, exchange, generation, and so on.

56:36.000 --> 56:43.000
The data movement can be organized both horizontally and vertically.

56:43.000 --> 56:49.000
In fact, everything depends on a specific business process and a given task.

56:49.000 --> 56:56.000
But the most typical data movement in an IT system is the movement along the contour.

56:56.000 --> 57:03.000
For example, the financial director collects reports from his departments,

57:03.000 --> 57:07.000
groups them, submits them to the management,

57:07.000 --> 57:11.000
considers all these reports, makes some instructions,

57:11.000 --> 57:13.000
sends them to the financial director,

57:13.000 --> 57:17.000
the financial director distributes them again to his departments.

57:17.000 --> 57:21.000
And so, in this cycle, the business process takes place.

57:21.000 --> 57:24.000
This is called the financial information contour.

57:24.000 --> 57:28.000
There are three levels of description of IT.

57:28.000 --> 57:30.000
This is the conceptual or content level,

57:30.000 --> 57:34.000
where the content of the subject area structure is described,

57:34.000 --> 57:37.000
in the area where IT operates.

57:37.000 --> 57:40.000
Next is the logical level of description,

57:40.000 --> 57:46.000
where the formalization of the model of the subject area is carried out.

57:46.000 --> 57:49.000
And finally, the physical level of description,

57:49.000 --> 57:53.000
which determines the way of implementing the IT model

57:53.000 --> 57:59.000
obtained at the conceptual and logical level in a technical device or devices.

57:59.000 --> 58:03.000
