The conceptual model of information technology consists of processes of obtaining,

01:01:23.000 --> 01:01:30.000
displaying, accumulating, processing, exchanging and forming knowledge and information.

01:01:30.000 --> 01:01:36.000
The dotted lines on the slide limit semantic information from data,

01:01:36.000 --> 01:01:40.000
which is described by syntax.

01:01:40.000 --> 01:01:45.000
That is, in fact, in the center, where the data are, we have a syntax.

01:01:45.000 --> 01:01:50.000
The information we are working with in the process of obtaining, that is, collection, preparation,

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:55.000
verification, well, maybe before inputting, all this has some semantic meaning.

01:01:55.000 --> 01:01:58.000
That is, it can answer the question of who, what, how, how much and where from.

01:01:58.000 --> 01:02:05.000
So, when we convert information into data, here, in fact, the syntax is in charge.

01:02:05.000 --> 01:02:12.000
Further, when we extract from the data, again, we get information in the display systems,

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:20.000
which can also have a semantic meaning and answer the questions of who, what, how.

01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:25.000
And already from the display or from the help of some other means of information systems,

01:02:25.000 --> 01:02:30.000
information technology, we can form knowledge that answers the question of how.

01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:35.000
We got one or another indicator, one or another property of the object and so on.

01:02:35.000 --> 01:02:41.000
The conceptual model of any technology should contain, in fact, information description of the subject area,

01:02:41.000 --> 01:02:43.000
in which business processes work.

01:02:43.000 --> 01:02:50.000
Therefore, in this scheme, we have highlighted layers of information technologies, processes, procedures and operations.

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:52.000
Let's repeat again.

01:02:52.000 --> 01:02:57.000
In the vertical curved line on the left, on the slide, processes and procedures are separated,

01:02:57.000 --> 01:03:03.000
working with information streams, in which some semantic meaning prevails.

01:03:03.000 --> 01:03:06.000
That is, information is converted into data.

01:03:07.000 --> 01:03:08.000
Or vice versa.

01:03:08.000 --> 01:03:14.000
In the center, working with data, the system of procedures and operations.

01:03:14.000 --> 01:03:22.000
And on the right, we again have information and knowledge, in which again the semantic aspect of information prevails.

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:30.000
If we consistently build a chain consisting of processes and procedures,

01:03:30.000 --> 01:03:36.000
then we will get a description of the process of information conversion to some final information product,

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:40.000
which can be some kind of documented management solution.

01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:45.000
That is, the initial process is the process of obtaining,

01:03:45.000 --> 01:03:51.000
and it begins with the collection procedure, displaying the subject area,

01:03:51.000 --> 01:03:56.000
for example, parameters, characteristics, the state of the control object.

01:03:56.000 --> 01:04:01.000
Further, the collected information must be prepared in the appropriate way,

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:08.000
that is, it must be analyzed, structured, checked for completeness, reliability, integrity, and so on.

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:12.000
After the preparation and verification stages,

01:04:12.000 --> 01:04:17.000
the information can be transmitted via communication channels in some traditional ways,

01:04:17.000 --> 01:04:24.000
such as telephone, courier, mail, telegraph, or with the help of information and communication technologies,

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:31.000
for the purpose of conversion, or, perhaps, the conversion algorithm can be immediately turned into data,

01:04:31.000 --> 01:04:35.000
in the process of, so-called, information input.

01:04:35.000 --> 01:04:41.000
This stage converts information into data in the form of digital codes,

01:04:41.000 --> 01:04:49.000
with the help of which this stage of input converts information into data in the form of digital codes,

01:04:49.000 --> 01:04:53.000
with the help of some specific physical phenomena.

01:04:53.000 --> 01:04:58.000
It is important to note that at these stages of the formation of information procedures,

01:04:58.000 --> 01:05:03.000
we usually deal with information that we can comprehend.

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:09.000
After the input, we already deal with data that can be processed,

01:05:09.000 --> 01:05:13.000
that is, converted, accumulated, or exchanged.

01:05:13.000 --> 01:05:20.000
The data processing process is associated with the main algorithms and computer calculations procedures.

01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:28.000
The exchange involves the transfer of data between all the processes that it is associated with at the level of data.

01:05:28.000 --> 01:05:32.000
The exchange also allows the transfer of data between users,

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:35.000
is used in the process of obtaining and displaying information,

01:05:35.000 --> 01:05:41.000
and also contributes to the process of accumulation of information coming from different sources.

01:05:41.000 --> 01:05:47.000
The main procedures of the exchange are the procedures of switching, routing, and transfer of data,

01:05:47.000 --> 01:05:52.000
which involves the presence of such operations as coding, decoding, modulation, demodulation,

01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:55.000
coordination, and signal amplification, and so on.

01:05:55.000 --> 01:06:03.000
The accumulation also allows you to convert data and store it for a long time,

01:06:03.000 --> 01:06:09.000
periodically updating, as well as extracting it in the right amount at the request of users.

01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:17.000
The accumulation usually involves the procedures of archiving, updating, searching, and updating data.

01:06:17.000 --> 01:06:22.000
The last operation is updating, adding other data to the data,

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:25.000
correcting old data, or destroying it.

01:06:25.000 --> 01:06:27.000
Next, we have the display.

01:06:27.000 --> 01:06:34.000
This procedure contains such procedures as converting data into a form that is convenient for perception,

01:06:34.000 --> 01:06:38.000
either in sound, text, or image, and so on.

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:44.000
The process of knowledge formation usually involves human activity.

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:54.000
In fact, we are dealing with the product of human thinking.

01:06:54.000 --> 01:06:58.000
However, so-called expert systems are being created,

01:06:58.000 --> 01:07:03.000
which allow or help or prompt a person

01:07:03.000 --> 01:07:09.000
how to form knowledge without consulting the services of specialists.

01:07:09.000 --> 01:07:12.000
Based on their algorithms,

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:20.000
they can form and display certain types of knowledge.

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:26.000
In fact, IT technology can help solve difficult-to-formalize tasks

01:07:26.000 --> 01:07:31.000
by automatizing the process of presenting knowledge.

01:07:31.000 --> 01:07:34.000
This is clearly shown in expert systems.

01:07:34.000 --> 01:07:40.000
The logical level of IT systems is a complex of interconnected models

01:07:40.000 --> 01:07:46.000
that formalize IT processes when data is transformed.

01:07:46.000 --> 01:07:49.000
This is also shown on the slide.

01:07:49.000 --> 01:07:52.000
It is also divided into a model of information display,

01:07:52.000 --> 01:07:56.000
a model of data exchange, data processing, data accumulation,

01:07:56.000 --> 01:08:01.000
a model of data acquisition, and a model of knowledge presentation.

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:08.000
Formalization in the form of models allows to connect the parameters of IT processes

01:08:08.000 --> 01:08:14.000
and allows to implement IT processes and procedures.

01:08:14.000 --> 01:08:21.000
The logical model of IT reflects the scheme of interconnection of IT processes.

01:08:21.000 --> 01:08:27.000
When processing data, all the main information processes are formed.

01:08:27.000 --> 01:08:32.000
Processing, exchange, accumulation of data, and knowledge presentation.

01:08:32.000 --> 01:08:35.000
What is the data processing model?

01:08:35.000 --> 01:08:41.000
The first is a formalized description of the processes of the organization of the processing.

01:08:41.000 --> 01:08:45.000
In fact, it is what we have to do with operating systems.

01:08:45.000 --> 01:08:48.000
The second is the transformation procedures,

01:08:48.000 --> 01:08:54.000
algorithms, programs, sorting, search, creation, update of some static or dynamic structures.

01:08:54.000 --> 01:08:58.000
And the third is the procedures of logical inference or modeling.

01:08:58.000 --> 01:09:05.000
The data exchange model contains a formal description of the procedures of the computing network,

01:09:05.000 --> 01:09:09.000
that is, transfer, encoding, modulation in the channels of communication,

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:13.000
commutation and routing from the protocol of the network exchange.

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:17.000
The data collection model is usually described using international standards,

01:09:17.000 --> 01:09:22.000
OSI, that is, in the interaction of open systems or local networks,

01:09:22.000 --> 01:09:26.000
as well as the specifications of the Internet network.

01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:32.000
The data accumulation model describes the system of data database management,

01:09:32.000 --> 01:09:35.000
as well as the information database itself,

01:09:35.000 --> 01:09:40.000
which can be defined as a database or a database of knowledge.

01:09:40.000 --> 01:09:45.000
The process of transition from the sensual, that is, information presentation to the physical,

01:09:45.000 --> 01:09:50.000
is carried out by a three-level information database model system.

01:09:50.000 --> 01:09:55.000
That is, from the conceptual one, which in what volume of information should be accumulated

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:58.000
when implementing information technology,

01:09:58.000 --> 01:10:02.000
logical, that is, the structure, self-connection of elements and information,

01:10:02.000 --> 01:10:08.000
and physical, that is, methods of data placement, access to them on machine carriers.

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:12.000
Next, let's consider the knowledge presentation model,

01:10:12.000 --> 01:10:17.000
which is chosen depending on the completeness, reproduction and content of the target area,

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:20.000
as well as the types of solvable tasks.

01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:27.000
At present, such knowledge presentation models are used as logical, algorithmic, semantic,

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:29.000
frame, integral.

01:10:29.000 --> 01:10:33.000
The data collection model is built on the basis of standards

01:10:33.000 --> 01:10:39.000
that recommend the structure of data and documents, as well as the data formats.

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:46.000
Finally, the information display model is built on the basis of various machine graphics formats

01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:51.000
and any other user graphical interface.

01:10:51.000 --> 01:10:54.000
In fact, this is an interface model,

01:10:54.000 --> 01:11:01.000
that is, how we interact with other parts of information technology, information systems.

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:07.000
Since the basic information processes operate with information, data and knowledge,

01:11:07.000 --> 01:11:10.000
the management takes place through the processes of obtaining,

01:11:10.000 --> 01:11:13.000
collection, preparation, input and display,

01:11:13.000 --> 01:11:17.000
construction of graphics, text, video, synthesis of speech.

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:21.000
Data management is carried out through the processing process,

01:11:21.000 --> 01:11:26.000
that is, in fact, the management of the organization of processing processes and transformation of information,

01:11:26.000 --> 01:11:29.000
as well as through the process of exchange,

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:35.000
routing and accumulation, that is, systems and databases.

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:44.000
Knowledge management is carried out through the system of management, obtaining and generating knowledge.

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:49.000
Next, let's consider the physical level of information technology description.

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:53.000
At the physical level, the description of information technology and systems

01:11:53.000 --> 01:11:57.000
is a software implementation.

01:11:57.000 --> 01:12:02.000
That is, the sub-system includes the sub-system of obtaining and displaying information and presenting knowledge,

01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:06.000
the sub-system of processing, the sub-system of data management and knowledge,

01:12:06.000 --> 01:12:10.000
the sub-system of data accumulation and the sub-system of data exchange.

01:12:10.000 --> 01:12:16.000
The slides show how the user and the developer work.

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:22.000
At the physical level, IT technologies are considered as a system consisting of large subsystems.

01:12:22.000 --> 01:12:26.000
Processing, exchange, data accumulation, obtaining and displaying information,

01:12:26.000 --> 01:12:29.000
presenting knowledge and data management and knowledge.

01:12:29.000 --> 01:12:32.000
Let's take a closer look at what the data processing subsystems are.

01:12:32.000 --> 01:12:36.000
They are built on the basis of different classes of computing systems

01:12:36.000 --> 01:12:39.000
and differ in power and performance.

01:12:39.000 --> 01:12:42.000
Depending on the needs of the solved tasks,

01:12:42.000 --> 01:12:46.000
large universal hardware computing systems can be used,

01:12:46.000 --> 01:12:51.000
such as mainframes, which are designed for processing large amounts of information.

01:12:51.000 --> 01:12:55.000
If some small amount of information is processed,

01:12:55.000 --> 01:13:02.000
then such software computing systems as personal computers or PCs can be used for this.

01:13:02.000 --> 01:13:07.000
Both servers and clients, i.e. workstations, are used in the network.

01:13:07.000 --> 01:13:12.000
The data exchange subsystem includes programs and devices,

01:13:12.000 --> 01:13:16.000
i.e. modems, amplifiers, commutators, cables, etc.,

01:13:16.000 --> 01:13:21.000
which create a computing network and perform commutation,

01:13:21.000 --> 01:13:24.000
routing and access to networks.

01:13:24.000 --> 01:13:28.000
Data accumulation subsystems are implemented using banks and databases

01:13:28.000 --> 01:13:33.000
on external devices of the computer that manages them.

01:13:33.000 --> 01:13:37.000
It is possible to organize both local databases,

01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:40.000
which are implemented on individual computers,

01:13:40.000 --> 01:13:43.000
and distributed databases,

01:13:43.000 --> 01:13:47.000
which are used in the network and distributed data processing.

01:13:47.000 --> 01:13:52.000
The information display and knowledge presentation subsystem

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:55.000
is used to form models of the subject area

01:13:55.000 --> 01:13:58.000
from its fragments and models of the solved tasks.

01:13:58.000 --> 01:14:05.000
At the design stage, the developer usually forms a complex of models of the solved tasks in the memory of the computer.

01:14:05.000 --> 01:14:12.000
At the operation stage, the user turns to the information display and knowledge presentation subsystem,

01:14:12.000 --> 01:14:18.000
and, based on the task set, chooses the appropriate solution model,

01:14:18.000 --> 01:14:22.000
after which other subsystems are included through the data management system.

01:14:22.000 --> 01:14:26.000
Finally, the data and knowledge management subsystem.

01:14:26.000 --> 01:14:29.000
As a rule, it is partially implemented on the same computers,

01:14:29.000 --> 01:14:31.000
that is, on one computer,

01:14:31.000 --> 01:14:34.000
on which all other subsystems are implemented,

01:14:34.000 --> 01:14:40.000
and partially can be implemented using the systems of organization of the processing process

01:14:40.000 --> 01:14:44.000
or using the databases management system.

01:14:44.000 --> 01:14:48.000
With large flows of information, special services are created,

01:14:48.000 --> 01:14:51.000
the so-called network administrators of databases.

01:14:51.000 --> 01:14:56.000
Let's consider the composition and classification of corporate information systems.

01:14:56.000 --> 01:14:58.000
Let's turn to the next slide,

01:14:58.000 --> 01:15:03.000
which shows the composition of the integrated corporate information system.

01:15:03.000 --> 01:15:07.000
Usually, functional and providing subsystems stand out.

01:15:07.000 --> 01:15:09.000
Functional subsystems,

01:15:09.000 --> 01:15:13.000
corporate information systems or KISS,

01:15:13.000 --> 01:15:17.000
informatively serve certain types of economic activities,

01:15:18.000 --> 01:15:23.000
that is, enterprises that are characteristic of its structural divisions or functions of management.

01:15:23.000 --> 01:15:29.000
For example, accounting, accounting, analysis, economic activities, technical preparation, planning, etc.

01:15:29.000 --> 01:15:34.000
The integration of functional subsystems into a single system is achieved

01:15:34.000 --> 01:15:38.000
by creating and functioning providing subsystems,

01:15:38.000 --> 01:15:45.000
such as information, mathematical, organizational, legal, technical, personnel and other subsystems.

01:15:45.000 --> 01:15:50.000
The functional structure of KISS is a complex of economic tasks

01:15:50.000 --> 01:15:56.000
with a high degree of information exchanges, that is, connections between these tasks.

01:15:56.000 --> 01:16:00.000
The next slide shows some of these tasks,

01:16:00.000 --> 01:16:03.000
depending on the level of management.

01:16:03.000 --> 01:16:08.000
For example, marketing at the strategic level is some new products and services,

01:16:08.000 --> 01:16:10.000
research and development.

01:16:10.000 --> 01:16:14.000
At the tactical level, it is analysis and planning of sales volumes.

01:16:14.000 --> 01:16:17.000
At the operational level, it is processing of customer orders,

01:16:17.000 --> 01:16:19.000
issuing of accounts, deposits, etc.

01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:25.000
The composition of functional subsystems is largely determined by the features of the economic system,

01:16:25.000 --> 01:16:32.000
its business property, forms of ownership, sizes and character of the enterprise or company.

01:16:32.000 --> 01:16:36.000
Functional subsystems are allocated for the implementation of the functions of management,

01:16:36.000 --> 01:16:40.000
such as forecasting, norming, planning,

01:16:40.000 --> 01:16:47.000
accounting and analysis, regulation, which is implemented at various levels of management

01:16:47.000 --> 01:16:55.000
and are combined into relevant management contours, such as marketing, production, logistics, finance.

01:16:55.000 --> 01:17:01.000
The subject structure of KISS is a subsystem of management of enterprise resources,

01:17:01.000 --> 01:17:05.000
that is, technical preparation of production, main and auxiliary production,

01:17:05.000 --> 01:17:09.000
quality of production, logistics, marketing, personnel.

01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:15.000
Functional subsystems cover all types of economic activities or business processes of the enterprise,

01:17:15.000 --> 01:17:19.000
that is, production, supply, supply, personnel, finance.

01:17:19.000 --> 01:17:26.000
Subject subsystems are mainly related to the operational level of management.

01:17:26.000 --> 01:17:30.000
As for the supporting subsystems of the corporate information system,

01:17:30.000 --> 01:17:36.000
they practically do not depend on the subject area and have their own specific functional structure,

01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:43.000
namely, information, mathematical, technical, organizational, personnel and other support.

01:17:43.000 --> 01:17:46.000
At the stage of development of the corporate information system,

01:17:46.000 --> 01:17:57.000
such supporting subsystems as legal, linguistic, technological and methodological support are attracted.

01:17:57.000 --> 01:18:03.000
The slide shows what supporting systems of the corporate information system are.

01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:07.000
That is, the object of management is the information system itself,

01:18:07.000 --> 01:18:12.000
and the functional structure is information support, mathematical, technical, organizational and personnel.

01:18:12.000 --> 01:18:15.000
What is it? Let's briefly go through them.

01:18:15.000 --> 01:18:20.000
Information support is a set of means and methods of building an information base.

01:18:20.000 --> 01:18:28.000
It consists of information arrays, structured data, documents, incoming, intermediate, outgoing,

01:18:28.000 --> 01:18:33.000
as well as rules and methods of subject area classification, coding,

01:18:33.000 --> 01:18:38.000
that is, from normative and verification documentation, operational information, some methodological materials.

01:18:38.000 --> 01:18:42.000
Mathematical support consists mainly of algorithmic support,

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:46.000
that is, models and algorithms, as well as software support,

01:18:46.000 --> 01:18:50.000
that is, what operating systems, what application software is used, and so on.

01:18:50.000 --> 01:18:55.000
Technical support is, in fact, computing technology, peripheral devices,

01:18:55.000 --> 01:18:59.000
network communications, org technology and some communication tools.

01:18:59.000 --> 01:19:03.000
Personnel support is training personnel,

01:19:03.000 --> 01:19:07.000
it is methodology, it is a program of courses necessary to maintain the capabilities

01:19:07.000 --> 01:19:11.000
and development of the corporate information system.

01:19:11.000 --> 01:19:18.000
Organizational support is a set of means and methods of organization, production, management

01:19:18.000 --> 01:19:22.000
at the stage of implementation of the corporate information system.

01:19:22.000 --> 01:19:25.000
That is, only when we implement KIS.

01:19:25.000 --> 01:19:29.000
This includes some industry-leading methodological materials,

01:19:29.000 --> 01:19:35.000
typical solutions, design documentation, typical application packages,

01:19:35.000 --> 01:19:40.000
general system or industry classifiers, technical and economic tasks and reasons,

01:19:40.000 --> 01:19:44.000
technical work projects, regular schedules, and so on.

01:19:44.000 --> 01:19:53.000
Legal support is related to the regulation of the creation and operation of the corporate information system.

01:19:53.000 --> 01:19:58.000
For example, the regulation of information that is part of the commercial secret.

01:19:58.000 --> 01:20:04.000
Each KIS and each enterprise may have its own specific features.

01:20:04.000 --> 01:20:12.000
Linguistic support is a set of language tools for successful interaction of various KIS subsystems.

01:20:12.000 --> 01:20:18.000
That is, the languages of the sub-BD, the application software, the rules of formalization of the natural language

01:20:18.000 --> 01:20:21.000
for compression or disclosure of text information, and so on.

01:20:21.000 --> 01:20:28.000
Finally, technological support is a variety of subsystems for processing various types of information

01:20:28.000 --> 01:20:36.000
at the stages of their appearance in the life or activity of the corporate information system.

01:20:36.000 --> 01:20:42.000
The most interesting for the manager are three information processing systems in KIS.

01:20:42.000 --> 01:20:49.000
This is the so-called OLTP, online transaction processing,

01:20:49.000 --> 01:20:56.000
in which the corporate information system works with small transactions,

01:20:56.000 --> 01:21:02.000
but with a fast-flowing flow, and the client needs the system to respond as quickly as possible.

01:21:03.000 --> 01:21:06.000
The analysis should be instantaneous.

01:21:06.000 --> 01:21:10.000
An example is the registration of visits to the website.

01:21:10.000 --> 01:21:15.000
It is so automated that we do not notice how it happens.

01:21:15.000 --> 01:21:20.000
Or the automation of the accounting, storage account, or the account of documents.

01:21:20.000 --> 01:21:22.000
All this is done on a flow.

01:21:22.000 --> 01:21:29.000
The second type of information processing system, which can also be involved in corporate information systems,

01:21:29.000 --> 01:21:32.000
is OLAP, online analytic processing.

01:21:32.000 --> 01:21:36.000
This requires a little more time.

01:21:36.000 --> 01:21:42.000
This is the analytical processing in real time, or the technology of analytical processing of information,

01:21:42.000 --> 01:21:49.000
the essence of which is in the composition of reports and documents, as well as their dynamic publication.

01:21:49.000 --> 01:21:56.000
It is usually used by analysts to carry out complex queries on the basis of data,

01:21:56.000 --> 01:22:01.000
to prepare business accounts for sales, marketing, and so on.

01:22:01.000 --> 01:22:06.000
The third type of information processing system, which is most common in KIS,

01:22:06.000 --> 01:22:20.000
is the intellectual analysis of data, or data mining, as it is called in the slang of IT specialists.

01:22:20.000 --> 01:22:24.000
This is a process of automatic search for patterns,

01:22:24.000 --> 01:22:27.000
that is, the detection of some hidden patterns,

