and now they are already bringing their products to the corporate level and are associated with ERP systems.

01:26:10.000 --> 01:26:16.000
Classification from the textbook of Trofimov, dedicated to information technologies in the economy,

01:26:16.000 --> 01:26:27.000
can be taken as a basis and used as a guide for choosing from an impressive amount of IT products and solutions

01:26:27.000 --> 01:26:35.000
accumulated by the business for some practical meaning and for the practice of management.

01:26:35.000 --> 01:26:42.000
According to this textbook, IT is classified in the sphere of operations of the management object,

01:26:42.000 --> 01:26:48.000
i.e. industrial enterprises, education, social sphere, banking, credit organizations.

01:26:48.000 --> 01:26:54.000
Further, it is a functional classification of the functional structure of information systems,

01:26:54.000 --> 01:27:01.000
i.e. automation of technical preparation of production, marketing, enterprise development strategy,

01:27:01.000 --> 01:27:07.000
economic planning, finance, material and technical supply, management of personnel, and others.

01:27:07.000 --> 01:27:14.000
In terms of organizational structure, IT systems can be distinguished from those systems

01:27:14.000 --> 01:27:19.000
that are focused on one automated workplace of the management personnel,

01:27:19.000 --> 01:27:25.000
as well as on complexes of interconnected ERPs, i.e. automated workplaces.

01:27:25.000 --> 01:27:32.000
Information systems are divided by borders into information systems of enterprises, organizations, industries,

01:27:32.000 --> 01:27:39.000
state, and even international information systems, such as the international system of transfers, SWIFT,

01:27:39.000 --> 01:27:41.000
which is used by all banks.

01:27:41.000 --> 01:27:51.000
In terms of integration, IT systems are classified as local, i.e. the use of isolated information space,

01:27:51.000 --> 01:27:57.000
partially integrated information systems, i.e. which have some common information space,

01:27:57.000 --> 01:28:01.000
and a fully integrated cooperative information system.

01:28:02.000 --> 01:28:11.000
In terms of IT architecture, IT systems are divided into IT systems with centralized architecture and construction,

01:28:11.000 --> 01:28:20.000
i.e. one data storage and processing center, or IT systems with distributed architecture,

01:28:20.000 --> 01:28:25.000
i.e. computer networks and the presence of many data processing and storage centers.

01:28:25.000 --> 01:28:34.000
In terms of specialization, IT systems are classified as IT systems for organizational and economic management,

01:28:34.000 --> 01:28:41.000
IT systems for automated training, i.e. e-learning system,

01:28:41.000 --> 01:28:47.000
automated management systems of organization resources, i.e. MRP and RP systems,

01:28:47.000 --> 01:28:54.000
automated systems for the technological processes of production of products, i.e. ASUTP,

01:28:54.000 --> 01:29:01.000
as well as specialized systems such as SAPR, automated design systems for design,

01:29:01.000 --> 01:29:04.000
production technology and other products.

01:29:04.000 --> 01:29:10.000
Finally, let's consider the last important element of corporate information systems,

01:29:10.000 --> 01:29:15.000
i.e. the lifecycle of information systems, i.e. the process of creating an information system,

01:29:15.000 --> 01:29:23.000
which is described using the following concepts, i.e. the lifecycle itself, phases, stages, stages,

01:29:23.000 --> 01:29:26.000
stages, processes, operations and elements.

01:29:26.000 --> 01:29:34.000
The main phases of the lifecycle of any corporate system are the phase of invention, development,

01:29:34.000 --> 01:29:37.000
operation and dismantling.

01:29:37.000 --> 01:29:42.000
The most important phases are the phase of invention and development,

01:29:42.000 --> 01:29:46.000
which are built from the following five stages, as a rule,

01:29:46.000 --> 01:29:53.000
i.e. the formation of requirements, development of concepts, technical tasks, technical project and implementation.

01:29:53.000 --> 01:29:59.000
The methodology of creating information systems is reflected in the normative documents,

01:29:59.000 --> 01:30:04.000
the majority of which have the power of international standards.

01:30:04.000 --> 01:30:09.000
Terminology, order, creation and implementation of requirements for parts,

01:30:09.000 --> 01:30:12.000
the composition of projects.

01:30:12.000 --> 01:30:19.000
The sequence of works related to the determination of the purposefulness of creation and industrial operation of an information system

01:30:19.000 --> 01:30:24.000
is defined in the form of a process, i.e. creation or manufacture,

01:30:24.000 --> 01:30:32.000
which has a hierarchical description and consists of stages, each of which includes stages,

01:30:32.000 --> 01:30:35.000
and they are, in turn, types of work.

01:30:35.000 --> 01:30:37.000
That is, such a matryoshka is obtained.

01:30:37.000 --> 01:30:45.000
As a fragment, we will consider in more detail the content of the process of creation and implementation of a corporate information system,

01:30:45.000 --> 01:30:50.000
which includes the following stages, stages and some types of work.

01:30:50.000 --> 01:30:55.000
The stage of forming requirements and development of concepts.

01:30:55.000 --> 01:31:03.000
The main purpose of the stages and work of these stages is to form a proposal based on the position of the customer

01:31:03.000 --> 01:31:10.000
and to propose the creation of a corporate information system with certain basic functions and technical characteristics.

01:31:10.000 --> 01:31:17.000
That is, what functionality is required for a particular customer and what should be the technical basis for this functionality.

01:31:17.000 --> 01:31:23.000
The main output documents of this stage are reports and technical and economic justification,

01:31:23.000 --> 01:31:30.000
the purposefulness of creating a corporate information system with selected functions and characteristics,

01:31:30.000 --> 01:31:36.000
as well as applications for the creation of KIS and the initial technical requirements for a corporate information system

01:31:36.000 --> 01:31:39.000
in the corresponding volume, usually to the state.

01:31:39.000 --> 01:31:44.000
Further, the stages of technical task and sketch design.

01:31:44.000 --> 01:31:53.000
The main purpose of these stages is to confirm the purposefulness and detailed examination of the possibility

01:31:53.000 --> 01:32:00.000
of creating an effective information system with functions and technical characteristics

01:32:00.000 --> 01:32:04.000
formulated in the form of initial technical requirements for the system.

01:32:04.000 --> 01:32:09.000
That is, what is the overall planning of all scientific and technical works,

01:32:09.000 --> 01:32:13.000
design and construction works, project installation and installation works,

01:32:13.000 --> 01:32:17.000
and the deadlines for their execution, the organization of the executors,

01:32:17.000 --> 01:32:21.000
the preparation of all the materials necessary for the project work.

01:32:21.000 --> 01:32:28.000
The output documents at this stage are the technical task for the creation of an information system

01:32:28.000 --> 01:32:32.000
containing technical requirements and a work schedule plan,

01:32:32.000 --> 01:32:37.000
which is agreed upon with the customer and the main executor,

01:32:37.000 --> 01:32:41.000
which will be used to implement the corporate information system,

01:32:41.000 --> 01:32:47.000
as well as clarification of economic justification and some solutions planned in the technical task,

01:32:47.000 --> 01:32:49.000
if necessary.

01:32:49.000 --> 01:32:56.000
A scientific and technical report containing the results of pre-project studies

01:32:56.000 --> 01:33:00.000
or some kind of sketch project of the information system is also possible.

01:33:00.000 --> 01:33:04.000
Further, the stage of technical projects.

01:33:04.000 --> 01:33:09.000
The purpose of the work carried out at this stage is to develop the basic technical solutions

01:33:09.000 --> 01:33:14.000
for the system being created and to finally determine the cost.

01:33:14.000 --> 01:33:20.000
The work of this stage is completed by the development of some general system solutions

01:33:20.000 --> 01:33:26.000
necessary and sufficient for the release of operational documentation for the system as a whole,

01:33:26.000 --> 01:33:29.000
that is, the project of the death documentation.

01:33:29.000 --> 01:33:36.000
Also, at this stage, we have, as a rule, a project of applications for the development of some new technical means.

01:33:36.000 --> 01:33:42.000
At this stage, the documentation of special mathematical and technical support is being developed,

01:33:42.000 --> 01:33:46.000
including technical tasks for programming.

01:33:46.000 --> 01:33:52.000
That is, at this stage, requirements for programmers are being formed.

01:33:52.000 --> 01:34:00.000
The main result of the work is the design of a technical project for the corporate information system.

01:34:00.000 --> 01:34:03.000
The work documentation is the next stage.

01:34:03.000 --> 01:34:10.000
The purpose of the work carried out at this stage is to release the work documentation for the system being created.

01:34:10.000 --> 01:34:16.000
The stage is completed by the release of the information system project consisting of the project documentation

01:34:16.000 --> 01:34:24.000
necessary and sufficient for the purchase, installation and installation of some sets of hardware and technical means of the system,

01:34:24.000 --> 01:34:32.000
as well as the documentation of the program and organizational support necessary and sufficient for the operation of the system as a whole.

01:34:32.000 --> 01:34:35.000
And finally, the stage of implementation.

01:34:35.000 --> 01:34:41.000
The purpose of this stage and the main result, in fact, is to transfer the operating system into industrial operation,

01:34:41.000 --> 01:34:47.000
as well as to obtain some objective, systematized data on the quality of the system,

01:34:47.000 --> 01:34:54.000
its current state and the real effect of the system based on the experience of its industrial operation.

01:34:54.000 --> 01:35:01.000
For this, the performance of the system as a whole and its individual elements are determined.

01:35:01.000 --> 01:35:07.000
The performance of the system as a whole is determined by the technical and economic efficiency of the system,

01:35:07.000 --> 01:35:13.000
the functional and algorithmic completeness of the system,

01:35:13.000 --> 01:35:21.000
and the social and psychological comfort for the personnel operating the corporate information system.

01:35:22.000 --> 01:35:32.000
So, we have considered both information technology and information systems from the stage of creation to the full life cycle,

01:35:32.000 --> 01:35:35.000
that is, to the stage of dismantling.

01:35:35.000 --> 01:35:38.000
Let's sum up some of the results of the second lecture.

01:35:38.000 --> 01:35:45.000
The first thing to pay attention to is that any modern corporate information system includes as components

01:35:45.000 --> 01:35:53.000
a set of other specialized information systems designed for certain purposes.

01:35:53.000 --> 01:35:57.000
For example, automation of the production process, support for decision-making,

01:35:57.000 --> 01:36:01.000
the formation of knowledge of the operating system, and so on.

01:36:01.000 --> 01:36:07.000
The second thing is that today information technology is more and more associated with some kind of final set of decisions

01:36:07.000 --> 01:36:09.000
on the automation of business processes,

01:36:09.000 --> 01:36:15.000
and information systems are more associated with some kind of set of products for the optimization of business processes

01:36:15.000 --> 01:36:17.000
and their strategic development.

01:36:17.000 --> 01:36:21.000
The third thing to pay attention to is that one of the most important aspects,

01:36:21.000 --> 01:36:28.000
which is often omitted from the view of managers when deciding to introduce a particular corporate information system,

01:36:28.000 --> 01:36:35.000
is the humiliation of the role of the human factor in favor of the development of some kind of technocratic.

01:36:35.000 --> 01:36:41.000
No matter how perfect the software provided by the company or manager,

01:36:41.000 --> 01:36:50.000
or how powerful the hardware device or hardware part of the technology may look,

01:36:50.000 --> 01:36:58.000
they all have zero value if they are not owned by specialists, employees, that is, staff.

01:36:58.000 --> 01:37:04.000
There is an idiom, if you bought something, then you own it.

01:37:04.000 --> 01:37:08.000
But if you did not own it, then you do not have it.

01:37:08.000 --> 01:37:13.000
This is the situation characteristic of most Russian enterprises,

01:37:13.000 --> 01:37:22.000
in which 80% of IT services are aimed at maintaining the resources of computing complexes and software,

01:37:22.000 --> 01:37:31.000
while abroad this figure, according to our agency S-News, is only 40%.

01:37:31.000 --> 01:37:38.000
That is, the main foreign IT services are not aimed at technology and software,

01:37:38.000 --> 01:37:45.000
but at training staff, working with clients, consulting, and so on.

01:37:45.000 --> 01:37:50.000
Another moment of truth is laid in the computing complexes themselves.

01:37:50.000 --> 01:37:54.000
If you remember the Moore's law, which we talked about at the beginning,

01:37:54.000 --> 01:37:59.000
then the voices of experts and specialists are heard more and more often

01:37:59.000 --> 01:38:02.000
related to the issue of the ecology of computing.

01:38:02.000 --> 01:38:08.000
This increases the concentration of computing power on the decreasing area of the microprocessor.

01:38:08.000 --> 01:38:16.000
That is, the density of energy in chips turns them into a small semblance of a nuclear system.

01:38:16.000 --> 01:38:23.000
That is, by increasing some software characteristics, we violate other ecological ones.

01:38:23.000 --> 01:38:29.000
It is no coincidence that one of the significant characteristics of the so-called data processing centers,

01:38:29.000 --> 01:38:34.000
that is, the CODs, is not so much the maintenance of stable energy consumption,

01:38:34.000 --> 01:38:39.000
but the amount of energy consumed per unit of computing.

01:38:39.000 --> 01:38:47.000
Therefore, in one concept, hardware, software, human, ecological, and other factors can be combined

01:38:47.000 --> 01:38:51.000
only under the aegis of some theoretical knowledge, a construct, a concept,

01:38:51.000 --> 01:39:01.000
which will help to optimize the use of resources and will allow to achieve business goals in an effective way.

01:39:01.000 --> 01:39:08.000
The fifth point is the conditional classification and the difficulties of using the concept of IT systems and IT technology

01:39:08.000 --> 01:39:11.000
are due to the nature of the concept of information.

01:39:11.000 --> 01:39:18.000
If the information is considered in the context of the process as a whole, then it corresponds more to IT technology.

01:39:18.000 --> 01:39:26.000
If the information is considered as an object localized and circulating along the contour of some system,

01:39:26.000 --> 01:39:30.000
then the concept of IT system is more suitable here.

01:39:30.000 --> 01:39:38.000
So, in the most general form, for a NUSH manager, the IT system is a product of theoretical knowledge

01:39:38.000 --> 01:39:44.000
implemented in human, hardware, software, and other resources and technologies,

01:39:44.000 --> 01:39:50.000
which allows him to make the optimal choice of solutions for business goals.

01:39:50.000 --> 01:39:56.000
IT products allow the manager to cope with the ever-increasing flow of information,

01:39:56.000 --> 01:40:00.000
understand and classify his subject area of ââactivity,

